author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: Man shot and killed outside of Kenner home
text:
KENNER, LA (WVUE) - Authorities are try to figure out who shot and killed a man in Kenner.
Police arrived at the scene in the 900 block of 27th Street around 11:15 Wednesday night.
Officers say they found the victim, Cornel Woods, 42, lying outside his home, with at least one gunshot wound.
First responders took him to a hospital, where he was later pronounced dead.
Investigators are searching for a possible suspect and motive.
Kenner Police Chief Michael J. Glaser urges anyone with information concerning Cornel Woods or this murder, to call the Kenner Police Detective Vincent Miranti at (504) 712-2330 or Crimestoppers at (504) 822-1111.
